{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Epigrafe in greco di IV sec. d.C. di Alesa (Sicilia) in versi e prosa, per la morte di Eirena Philandros, \"carissima a Botis boio-celtico\"","Manganaro Perrone","2006","\u003Cspan>Giacomo Manganaro Perrone, «Epigrafe in greco di IV sec. d.C. di Alesa (Sicilia) in versi e prosa, per la morte di Eirena Philandros, “carissima a Botis boio-celtico”», \u003Ci>Zeitschrift für Papyrologie und Epigraphik\u003C/i> 158 (2006): 89–92\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/6KPB9V5B",[8,178],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":27,"handNote":34,"date":104,"places":110,"geo":120,"provenance":112,"provenanceGeo":124,"country":127,"region":128,"settlement":112,"repository":129,"idno":133,"textLang":136,"tmNumber":140,"facsimile":141,"letterHeights":148,"publications":149,"zotero":155,"keywords":161,"html":172,"bibl":173},"ISic003337","Funerary inscription for Eirena",{"_":12},"edited",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"marble\n                                    ","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html","",{"layout":28},{"p":29,"rs":30,"damage":26},"Ten lines of Greek filling the available space, decreasing notably in size in the second five lines",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":35,"dimensions":36},"The letters are engraved in a fairly plain, square fashion, with simple serifs. Alpha is mostly with broken bar, sometimes with an extended upper serif, although there is a straight bar example in line 7 and in lines 8 and 10 straight bar descending to left foot; beta is closed, with larger lower eye, generally horizontal along the base; delta varies between regular triangle and oblique lower bar with extended serif above; epsilon has straight bars of equal length, except for instances in lines 9 and 10 when it is lunate; theta is ovoid with connecting straight bar; kappa has short tails; lambda sometimes has an extended upper serif; mu varies between a form with vertical first and last hastae and short middle strokes meeting above the line and cursive form comparable to a lower-case mu in line 9; omicron is full size in the first few lines, but increasingly is smaller and mid-line; sigma is consistently lunate, but more often formed of three straight strokes; less often a single curved stroke; omega is consistently lunate, and sometimes smaller and mid-line. The eta and nu are in ligature in lines 5, 6 and 7. In line 5 the omicron in the final word is inscribed above the other letters (due to omission?). The last two/three words of the last line are enclosed between a pair of christograms. Small hedera occur in lines 1, 3, 5, and 10.",[37,43,47,51,55,58,62,66,70,74,78,82,85,88,91,94,96,99,102],{"type":38,"l":39,"from":40,"to":40,"h":41,"unit":42},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","12-18","mm",{"type":38,"l":44,"from":45,"to":45,"h":46,"unit":42},"Line 2","line2","14-19",{"type":38,"l":48,"from":49,"to":49,"h":50,"unit":42},"Line 3","line3","12-22",{"type":38,"l":52,"from":53,"to":53,"h":54,"unit":42},"Line 4","line4","8-22",{"type":38,"l":56,"from":57,"to":57,"h":41,"unit":42},"Line 5","line5",{"type":38,"l":59,"from":60,"to":60,"h":61,"unit":42},"Line 6","line6","9-16",{"type":38,"l":63,"from":64,"to":64,"h":65,"unit":42},"Line 7","line7","7-14",{"type":38,"l":67,"from":68,"to":68,"h":69,"unit":42},"Line 8","line8","6-12",{"type":38,"l":71,"from":72,"to":72,"h":73,"unit":42},"Line 9","line9","6-10",{"type":38,"l":75,"from":76,"to":76,"h":77,"unit":42},"Line 10","line10","5-13",{"type":79,"l":80,"from":40,"to":45,"h":81,"unit":42},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","10-15",{"type":79,"l":83,"from":45,"to":49,"h":84,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","3-7",{"type":79,"l":86,"from":49,"to":53,"h":87,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 3 to 4","5-15",{"type":79,"l":89,"from":53,"to":57,"h":90,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 4 to 5","4-10",{"type":79,"l":92,"from":57,"to":60,"h":93,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 5 to 6","2-7",{"type":79,"l":95,"from":60,"to":64,"h":93,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 6 to 7",{"type":79,"l":97,"from":64,"to":68,"h":98,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 7 to 8","1-6",{"type":79,"l":100,"from":68,"to":72,"h":101,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 8 to 9","1-5",{"type":79,"l":103,"from":72,"to":76,"h":101,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 9 to 10",{"_":105,"notBefore":106,"notAfter":107,"evidence":108,"precision":109},"Later 4th — 5th century CE (The tombs of the necropolis are dated to the late 4th and 5th century CE (Tigano 2008b: 49) and the inscription easily fits within this date range.",351,500,"context","low",[111,115],{"_":112,"type":113,"ref":114},"Halaesa","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":116,"type":117,"ref":118,"offset":119},"Castel di Tusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[121],[122,123],37.99907,14.26197,[125,126],38.007468,14.257626,"Italy","Sicily",{"_":130,"role":131,"ref":132},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":134,"type":135},"ME 20272","inventory",{"_":137,"mainLang":138,"languages":139},"Ancient Greek","grc",[137],"645584",{"n":142,"url":143,"height":144,"width":145,"desc":146,"surfaceType":147},"screen","ISic003337_tiled.tif","3387px","5310px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina","front",[],[150,151,152,153,154],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 